  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Is zero a rational number? Can you write it in the form <m>\frac{p}{q}</m> where <m>p</m> and <m>q</m> are integers and <m>q \neq 0</m>?
        </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
      <p>
        Zero can be written in the form <m>\frac{p}{q}</m> = <m>\frac{0}{1}</m>. Hence it is a rational number.
      </p>
    </solution>
    </exercise>

